quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  8,41,"Know that whatever spoils you take, one-fifth is for God and the Messenger, his close relatives, orphans, the poor, and ňĻneedyňļ travellers, if you ňĻtrulyňļ believe in God and what We revealed to Our servant on that decisive day when the two armies met ňĻat Badrňļ. And God is Most Capable of everything"
  8,42,"ňĻRememberňļ when you were on the near side of the valley, your enemy on the far side, and the caravan was below you. Even if the two armies had made an appointment ňĻto meetňļ, both would have certainly missed it.¬†Still it transpired so God may establish what He had destined‚ÄĒthat those who were to perish and those who were to survive might do so after the truth had been made clear to both. Surely God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,43,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when God showed them in your dream as few in number. Had He shown them to you as many, you ňĻbelieversňļ would have certainly faltered and disputed in the matter. But God spared you ňĻfrom thatňļ. Surely He knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  8,44,"Then when your armies met, God made them appear as few in your eyes, and made you appear as few in theirs, so God may establish what He had destined. And to God ňĻallňļ matters will be returned ňĻfor judgmentňļ"
  8,45,"O believers! When you face an enemy, stand firm and remember God often so you may triumph"
  8,46,"Obey God and His Messenger and do not dispute with one another, or you would be discouraged and weakened. Persevere! Surely God is with those who persevere"
  8,47,"Do not be like those ňĻpagansňļ who left their homes arrogantly, only to be seen by people and to hinder others from God‚Äôs Path. And God is Fully Aware of what they do"
  8,48,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Satan made their ňĻevilňļ deeds appealing to them, and said, ‚ÄúNo one can overcome you today. I am surely by your side.‚ÄĚ But when the two forces faced off, he cowered and said, ‚ÄúI have absolutely nothing to do with you. I certainly see what you do not see. I truly fear God, for God is severe in punishment.‚ÄĚ"
  8,49,"ňĻRememberňļ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, ‚ÄúThese ňĻbelieversňļ are deluded by their faith.‚ÄĚ But whoever puts their trust in God, surely God is Almighty, All-Wise"
  8,50,"If only you could see when the angels take the souls of the disbelievers, beating their faces and backs, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúTaste the torment of burning"
  8,51,This is ňĻthe rewardňļ for what your hands have done. And God is never unjust to ňĻHisňļ creation.‚ÄĚ
  8,52,"Their fate is that of the people of Pharaoh and those before them‚ÄĒthey all disbelieved in God‚Äôs signs, so God seized them for their sins. Indeed, God is All-Powerful, severe in punishment"
  8,53,"This is because God would never discontinue His favour to a people until they discontinue their faith. Surely God is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  8,54,"That was the case with Pharaoh‚Äôs people and those before them‚ÄĒthey all rejected the signs of their Lord, so We destroyed them for their sins and drowned Pharaoh‚Äôs people. They were all wrongdoers"
  8,55,"Indeed, the worst of all beings in the sight of God are those who persist in disbelief, never to have faith‚ÄĒ"
  8,56,"ňĻnamelyňļ those with whom you ňĻO Prophetňļ have entered into treaties, but they violate them every time, not fearing the consequences"
  8,57,"If you ever encounter them in battle, make a fearsome example of them, so perhaps those who would follow them may be deterred"
  8,58,"And if you ňĻO Prophetňļ see signs of betrayal by a people, respond by openly terminating your treaty with them. Surely God does not like those who betray"
  8,59,Do not let those disbelievers¬†think they are not within reach. They will have no escape
  8,60,Prepare against them what you ňĻbelieversňļ can of ňĻmilitaryňļ power and cavalry to deter God‚Äôs enemies and your enemies as well as other enemies unknown to you but known to God. Whatever you spend in the cause of God will be paid to you in full and you will not be wronged